name: Jalen Thompson
description: Coach Kliff Kingsbury said Friday that Thompson (ankle) aggravated the same ankle injury that landed him on injured reserve earlier this season in Thursday's loss to Seattle, Kyle Odegard of the Cardinals' official site reports.

name: Kyler Murray
description: Murray suffered an AC joint injury in his throwing shoulder during Thursday's loss to Seattle, but the Cardinals expect him to be fine for their next game, a Week 12 matchup with the Patriots on Nov. 29, NFL Network's Ian Rapoport reports.

name: Julio Jones
description: Interim coach Raheem Morris said Monday that Jones (hamstring) could be a "game-time decision" Week 12, William McFadden of the Falcons' official site reports.

name: Mykal Walker
description: Walker (hamstring) is questionable to return to Sunday's matchup against New Orleans.

name: J.K. Dobbins
description: Dobbins (illness) will be placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list after testing positive Monday, Mike Garafolo of NFL Network reports.

name: Mark Ingram II
description: Ingram tested positive for COVID-19 on Monday and will be placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list, Mike Garafolo of NFL Network reports.

name: John Brown
description: Coach Sean McDermott said Monday that Brown tweaked his ankle during Sunday's 32-30 loss to the Cardinals, Maddy Glab of the Bills' official site reports.

name: AJ Epenesa
description: Epenesa was ruled out for the rest of Sunday's game versus the Cardinals after suffering a concussion.

name: Christian McCaffrey
description: Coach Matt Rhule said Monday that McCaffrey is "week to week" ahead of the Week 12 matchup against Minnesota, Joe Person of The Athletic reports.

name: Teddy Bridgewater
description: Coach Matt Rhule said Monday that he expects Bridgewater to participate in Wednesday's practice, John Oehser of the Jaguars' official site reports.

name: Dennis Daley
description: Daley suffered a concussion during Sunday's game against the Lions, Alaina Getzenberg of The Charlotte Observer reports.

name: Eddie Jackson
description: Jackson (undisclosed) was placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list Monday, Adam Hoge of NBC Sports Chicago reports.

name: David Montgomery
description: Montgomery (concussion) is present for the portion of Monday's practice open to the media, Colleen Kane of the Chicago Tribune reports.

name: Mitchell Trubisky
description: Coach Matt Nagy said Monday that he's not yet ready to name Trubisky (shoulder) or Nick Foles (hip) the starter for Sunday's game against the Packers, Jeff Dickerson of ESPN.com reports.

name: Nick Foles
description: Coach Matt Nagy said Monday that it's "too soon" to announce whether Foles (hip) or Mitchell Trubisky (shoulder) will start Sunday's game against the Packers, Jeff Dickerson of ESPN.com reports.

name: Akiem Hicks
description: Hicks suffered a strained right hamstring in Monday's loss to the Vikings, Adam Jahns of The Athletic reports.

name: Joe Burrow
description: The Bengals placed Burrow (torn ACL) on injured reserve Monday.

name: Denzel Ward
description: Coach Kevin Stefanski said Ward will undergo an MRI on Monday to determine the extent of his calf injury, Mary Kay Cabot of The Cleveland Plain Dealer reports.

name: Ronnie Harrison Jr.
description: Harrison suffered a bone bruse on his knee during Sunday's win over the Eagles, Jeremy Fowler of ESPN.com reports.

name: Anthony Brown
description: Brown (ribs) isn't expected to play in Thursday's game against Washington, Michael Gehlken of The Dallas Morning News reports.

name: Trey Marshall
description: Marshall was forced out of Sunday's game against the Dolphins with a lower leg injury, Patrick Smyth of the Broncos' official site reports.

name: Jeff Okudah
description: Okudah exited Sunday's game against the Panthers with shoulder injury.

name: Mike Ford
description: Ford exited Sunday's game against the Panthers to be evaluated for a concussion.

name: Corey Linsley
description: Linsley (back) is ruled out to return to Sunday's game against the Colts.

name: Randall Cobb
description: Cobb (toe) is in danger of being placed on injured reserve, Aaron Wilson of the Houston Chronicle reports.

name: Kenny Stills
description: Stills (quadriceps) hasn't been ruled out for Thursday's game against the Lions after getting the results of Sunday's MRI back, Aaron Wilson of the Houston Chronicle reports.

name: P.J. Hall
description: Hall was forced out of Sunday's game against the Patriots with a chest injury.

name: Andrew Norwell
description: Coach Doug Marrone said he doesn't expect Norwell (arm) to play Sunday against the Browns, John Shipley of SI.com reports.

name: Daniel Thomas
description: Coach Doug Marrone said Monday that Thomas (arm) will miss "considerable time," John Oehser of the Jaguars' official site reports.

name: D.J. Hayden
description: Coach Doug Marrone said Monday that Hayden (knee) will miss "considerable time," Mike Garafolo of NFL Network reports.

name: Josh Allen
description: Coach Doug Marrone said Monday that Allen avoided ligament damage in his knee but will miss "considerable time," John Oehser of the Jaguars' official site reports.

name: Chris Claybrooks
description: Claybrooks suffered a groin injury during Sunday's loss to the Steelers.

name: Byron Pringle
description: Pringle (ankle) is questionable to return to Sunday's game against the Raiders.

name: Uchenna Nwosu
description: Nwosu sprained the AC join in his shoulder during Sunday's win over the Jets and is expected to miss about three weeks, Aaron Wilson of the Houston Chronicle reports.

name: Casey Hayward Jr.
description: Hayward suffered a groin injury during Sunday's game against the Jets.

name: Brian Allen
description: Allen (knee) is doubtful for Monday's game against the Buccaneers.

name: Solomon Kindley
description: Kindley was forced out of Sunday's game against the Broncos with a foot injury, Travis Wingfield of the Dolphins' official site reports.

name: Rex Burkhead
description: Burkhead was forced outof Sunday's game against the Texans with a knee injury.

name: Deonte Harris
description: Harris has a stinger as is questionable to return to Sunday's matchup against the Falcons, Nick Underhill of NewOrleans.Football reports.

name: Andrus Peat
description: Peat (concussion) has been ruled out for the remainder of Sunday's matchup against the Falcons, John DeShazier of the Saints' official site reports.

name: Trevor Siemian
description: reserve-cel

name: Kevin Zeitler
description: Zeitler (concussion) has been ruled out for the remainder of Sunday's matchup against the Eagles, Dan Salomone of the Giants' official site reports.

name: George Fant
description: Fant (ankle) will undergo an MRI on Monday, Rich Cimini of ESPN.com reports.

name: La'Mical Perine
description: Perine suffered an ankle injury during Sunday's game at Denver, Al Iannazzone of Newsday reports.

name: Pat Elflein
description: reserve-cel

name: Jason Peters
description: Coach Doug Pederson said Peters (undisclosed) remains Philadelphia's starting left tackle, Les Bowen of the Philadelphia Daily News reports.

name: Cre'Von LeBlanc
description: LeBlanc suffered a high-ankle sprain during Sunday's loss to the Browns and is expected to land on injured reserve, Tom Pelissero of NFL Network reports.

name: Lane Johnson
description: Johnson left Sunday's game against the Browns with a shoulder injury.

name: JuJu Smith-Schuster
description: Smith-Schuster suffered a toe injury during Sunday's game against the Jaguars, Brooke Pryor of ESPN.com reports.

name: Zach Gentry
description: Gentry won't return to Sunday's game against the Jaguars due to a knee injury.

name: D.J. Jones
description: Jones was placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list Sunday, Jennifer Lee Chan of NBC Sports Bay Area reports.

name: Jordan Willis
description: Willis was placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list Sunday, Jennifer Lee Chan of NBC Sports Bay Area reports.

name: Deebo Samuel
description: Coach Kyle Shanahan is hopeful Samuel (hamstring) will be available for the 49ers' next game Sunday, Nov. 29 against the Rams, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.

name: Tevin Coleman
description: Coach Kyle Shanahan hopes Coleman (knee) will be available for the 49ers' next game Sunday, Nov. 29 against the Rams, Nick Wagoner of ESPN.com reports.

name: Jerick McKinnon
description: Coach Kyle Shanahan said after Sunday's 27-13 loss to the Saints that McKinnon suffered a stinger late in the game, Jennifer Lee Chan of NBC Sports reports.

name: Greg Olsen
description: Olsen (foot), who suffered a ruptured plantar fascia to his left foot in Thursday's 28-21 win over the Cardinals, is expected to miss about six weeks to two months, Ian Rapoport of NFL Network reports.

name: Brandon Shell
description: Coach Pete Carroll said Thursday that Shell suffered an ankle sprain, Bob Condotta of The Seattle Times reports.

name: Ali Marpet
description: Marpet (concussion) has been ruled out for Tampa Bay's Monday night matchup against the Rams.

name: Tanner Hudson
description: Hudson (personal) has been ruled out for Monday's game against the Rams, Greg Auman of The Athletic reports.

name: Jayon Brown
description: Brown suffered a dislocated and fractured elbow during Sunday's win over Baltimore and has been ruled out for the rest of the season, Ian Rapoport of NFL Network reports.
